	<h1>Stop Asian Hate</h1>

	<p> The United States has a long history of social and political movements that have led to major protests throughout the country including the Stop Asian Hate, which began on Friday, March 26, 2021. It occurred in multiple cities and was sparked by: Anti-Asian racism and hate crimes. The protest led to protests against anti-Asian hate crimes and discrimination, calls for increased awareness and action to combat racism towards Asian Americans.</p>

